definitions.definition: A character identical or nearly identical in appearance to another, but which differs in the meaning it represents; thus, in character encoding terms, a character with an identical or near-identical glyph , or the glyph itself.
examples: The homoglyphs I (uppercase i) and l (lowercase L) confused many who typed in the URL.

main_definition: ( linguistics , computing ) A character identical or nearly identical in appearance to another, but which differs in the meaning it represents; thus, in character encoding terms, a character with an identical or near-identical glyph , or the glyph itself.
